text: Ksenia Yevgenyevna Aleshina (; born 28 January 2003) is a Russian tennis player. Aleshina has a career high ITF junior combined ranking of 366 achieved on 28 January 2019. Aleshina made her WTA main draw debut at the 2019 Baltic Open in the doubles draw partnering Kamilla Bartone. ==References== ==External links== * Category:2003 births Category:Living people Category:Russian female tennis players
